WEBVTT

00:05.396 --> 00:07.790
♪

00:31.466 --> 00:33.468
♪

00:51.094 --> 00:52.704
[entry bells chime]

00:52.748 --> 00:54.924
Mmm...

00:54.967 --> 00:57.013
So, what do you think
of our new neighborhood?

00:57.057 --> 00:59.407
-Downtown River Creek. Ah.
-[sirens wailing in distance]

00:59.450 --> 01:01.931
Got to say,
sucks on a big one, Dad.

01:01.974 --> 01:03.324
This side of town is poor.

01:03.367 --> 01:05.630
My mood is poor
because we're poor.

01:05.674 --> 01:07.110
Come on!

01:07.154 --> 01:10.113
Any moment now, I'm gonna
come up with a kick-ass idea

01:10.157 --> 01:12.594
that will make us
moderately rich again.

01:12.637 --> 01:15.466
So, in the meantime,
let's just roll with it.

01:15.510 --> 01:17.729
Yeah, you just got to know
where to step.

01:17.773 --> 01:19.862
Like... not there.

01:20.776 --> 01:22.169
-Coffee shop.
-Bar.

01:22.212 --> 01:24.475
-Nail shop.
-Coffee shop.

01:24.519 --> 01:25.694
-Bar.
-Nail shop.

01:25.737 --> 01:27.217
Thrift shop. Huh?

01:27.261 --> 01:29.480
Oh, zippers on sweatpants.

01:29.524 --> 01:30.612
Huh.

01:34.094 --> 01:36.096
FREDDIE:
Kids, come into the kitchen!

01:38.881 --> 01:40.883
[sizzling]

01:42.667 --> 01:44.408
Cool! Fried catfish.

01:44.452 --> 01:46.454
So, what's coming up
this weekend?

01:46.497 --> 01:47.585
Chinese New Year.

01:47.629 --> 01:49.152
Like, really new.

01:49.196 --> 01:50.675
Like, an all-new animal,

01:50.719 --> 01:53.809
not just new to the calendar
but new to the world.

01:53.852 --> 01:56.072
No, it's your mom's birthday.

01:57.334 --> 01:59.684
Come on, you guys need to have
your own ideas for presents.

01:59.728 --> 02:01.556
So what are they?

02:01.599 --> 02:04.167
Eh, physical gifts are stupid.

02:04.211 --> 02:06.038
It's not like she has
a thing she collects,

02:06.082 --> 02:07.344
like you have neti pots.

02:07.388 --> 02:09.868
Okay, listen, I actually
hate neti pots, okay?

02:09.912 --> 02:12.044
People get me one
for every special day.

02:12.088 --> 02:14.438
Look, Father's Day,
Father's Day.

02:14.482 --> 02:16.440
27th through 33rd birthdays.
Oh,

02:16.484 --> 02:18.312
here's Christmas, Christmas,
etcetera, etcetera.

02:18.355 --> 02:20.705
Look, I don't want your mom
to feel how these make me feel.

02:20.749 --> 02:22.403
Okay? So put on
your thinking caps.

02:22.446 --> 02:24.056
So, what are you gonna get her?

02:24.100 --> 02:25.580
Oh, well, I'm glad you asked.

02:25.623 --> 02:27.234
See, I'm-I'm very attuned
to people.

02:27.277 --> 02:30.585
I notice things.
I sense what people really want.

02:30.628 --> 02:33.457
Not to be a dick or anything,
but I got to say,

02:33.501 --> 02:35.590
you're not a good a dad
as you think.

02:35.633 --> 02:38.549
What? That's absurd.
Right, Ollie?

02:38.593 --> 02:40.247
I don't know, man.

02:40.290 --> 02:42.423
You care so much
what people think of you

02:42.466 --> 02:45.382
that you ruin what they think
with your caring.

02:45.426 --> 02:46.905
[chuckles]:
Oh, my God.

02:46.949 --> 02:48.298
You guys are so wrong.

02:48.342 --> 02:50.387
I am the best gift giver.
Hello.

02:50.431 --> 02:51.910
And I'll prove it.

02:51.954 --> 02:53.695
I'm getting her...

02:53.738 --> 02:55.392
those sweatpants.

02:55.436 --> 02:56.785
Which sweaty pants?

02:56.828 --> 02:58.830
People look bad
in sweatpants, okay?

02:58.874 --> 03:00.267
It means they gave up on life.

03:00.310 --> 03:01.311
Oh, no.

03:01.355 --> 03:03.357
A woman looks best when relaxed.

03:03.400 --> 03:06.186
So I'll get her the sweatpants
and you two will come up

03:06.229 --> 03:08.579
with separate, nice presents.

03:08.623 --> 03:11.930
And save half the catfish
for your mom's lunch. Thank you.

03:14.411 --> 03:16.370
[applause on TV]

03:16.413 --> 03:19.199
Hey, Deb, you finish
that floor model yet?

03:19.242 --> 03:21.810
[grunts]
Working on it, Daddie.

03:21.853 --> 03:23.464
Just a few more tweaks,

03:23.507 --> 03:26.858
and this floor model assembly
robot will do it for us.

03:26.902 --> 03:29.339
I didn't ask for a robot
to assemble it, hon.

03:29.383 --> 03:31.254
I asked you to.

03:31.298 --> 03:33.343
Dad!

03:33.387 --> 03:36.825
You are wasting
my engineering genius here.

03:36.868 --> 03:40.089
[groaning]: I could be coming up
with kick-ass ideas

03:40.132 --> 03:43.440
to change the world and make us
all moderately rich and shit!

03:43.484 --> 03:45.529
Oh, hell.

03:45.573 --> 03:49.490
Here comes the only thing me
and Freddie can agree on--

03:49.533 --> 03:53.102
your bad news
best friend, Tonya.

03:53.145 --> 03:54.190
Cool.

03:56.192 --> 03:57.715
Wow.

03:57.759 --> 03:59.978
The place hasn't changed
since we were kids.

04:00.022 --> 04:02.807
Debbie, how about a lunch place
with drinks?

04:02.851 --> 04:04.548
Say, a bar?

04:04.592 --> 04:07.159
Uh, yes drinks, no to the bar.

04:07.203 --> 04:08.987
Let's keep it more casual.
Keep it tenna.

04:09.031 --> 04:10.162
What's tenna?

04:10.206 --> 04:11.381
Like the shoe.

04:11.425 --> 04:13.601
Nobody says "tennis shoes."

04:13.644 --> 04:16.386
She's been trying to get "tenna"
going for a while.

04:16.430 --> 04:19.346
Whatever. Deb, I heard of
a place right here, downtown,

04:19.389 --> 04:24.089
with double, uh, deep-fried,
uh, taco, uh, hot dogs.

04:24.133 --> 04:26.178
Debbie is in!

04:27.832 --> 04:30.313
Debbie is not in!

04:30.357 --> 04:31.880
Aw.

04:31.923 --> 04:34.317
All this dumb trucks
are blocking my parking

04:34.361 --> 04:35.753
and stealing my business.

04:35.797 --> 04:37.189
Do something, horse cop.

04:37.233 --> 04:39.235
Ma'am, I'm on my lunch break.

04:39.279 --> 04:41.716
So if you can hold that
complaint for ten minutes,

04:41.759 --> 04:43.326
I can eat my food.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.285
TONYA:
Ugh.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.764
Sorry about this, babe.

04:46.808 --> 04:48.766
Let's just... [groans]
let's just do this.

04:48.810 --> 04:50.768
TONYA:
Tick, tock.

04:50.812 --> 04:53.205
-DEBBIE: [groans] Come on!
-TONYA: Tick, tock. Tick...

04:53.249 --> 04:55.512
This here
is the pickup line, gals.

04:55.556 --> 04:57.297
Oh, shit.
Okay, this one, this one.

04:57.340 --> 04:59.342
[Debbie groans]

05:01.083 --> 05:03.520
-Move, move, move, move, move.
-[groans]

05:03.564 --> 05:05.174
Finally. All right, all right,
all right. Here we go.

05:05.217 --> 05:06.610
Um, I'll have the...

05:06.654 --> 05:08.656
FYI, we're out of
our signature dish

05:08.699 --> 05:10.092
that we should know
everyone wants:

05:10.135 --> 05:11.441
the double deep-fried taco
hot dogs.

05:11.485 --> 05:14.270
-We're out of that. Go!
-Okay, uh...

05:14.314 --> 05:16.881
Just put ten dollars of bacon
on a bun, okay?

05:16.925 --> 05:19.014
And then throw in some cheese
in a burger patty.

05:19.057 --> 05:20.145
And four beers.

05:20.189 --> 05:22.887
No alcohol in food truck land.
Go!

05:22.931 --> 05:24.454
-Oh! Oh.
-Oh, gosh. Oh, God. Oh, god.

05:24.498 --> 05:26.021
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
-[Tonya groans]

05:26.064 --> 05:29.372
The irritation and,
like, impossibility are

05:29.416 --> 05:31.853
what makes it so fun.

05:31.896 --> 05:33.376
[chuckles]
So street.

05:33.420 --> 05:34.682
Ugh.

05:34.725 --> 05:36.727
Street food culture
is a great way

05:36.771 --> 05:38.729
to get back in touch
with our places.

05:38.773 --> 05:41.558
I really like seeing people
learning to eat again,

05:41.602 --> 05:43.299
city style.

05:43.343 --> 05:47.303
A carne asada taco is
a great way to connect with...

05:47.347 --> 05:50.219
Shut the fuck up.

05:50.262 --> 05:51.960
What the F is wrong with you?

05:52.003 --> 05:54.441
Why can't you just relax
and enjoy this super cool,

05:54.484 --> 05:57.182
fun experience, this perk
of living on the north side?

05:57.226 --> 05:58.488
Just be cool.

05:58.532 --> 06:02.405
Don't activate me, Jame.

06:02.449 --> 06:04.538
I'm covered in food
in the hot sun--

06:04.581 --> 06:06.278
no awnings in sight--

06:06.322 --> 06:08.411
sitting in a parking lot
with a bush in my back

06:08.455 --> 06:09.891
and a homeless man
stealing my napkin

06:09.934 --> 06:12.110
so he can wipe his ass.

06:12.154 --> 06:13.416
No, it's fine.
Go ahead.

06:14.417 --> 06:16.419
And you want to know
the worst part?

06:16.463 --> 06:18.813
-No drinks.
-No drinks!

06:19.770 --> 06:21.642
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:21.685 --> 06:24.340
Tonya, I see...

06:24.384 --> 06:27.517
a demand that ain't
being supplied.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.432
[chuckles]

06:33.958 --> 06:35.395
[entry bells chime]

06:36.483 --> 06:38.049
Uh, yeah, excuse me.

06:38.093 --> 06:39.921
Yesterday, there were some
sweatpants in the window.

06:39.964 --> 06:42.576
Uh, tenna pants.
You know, casual attire.

06:42.619 --> 06:45.492
Another woman just purchased
them, right there.

06:45.535 --> 06:47.450
♪

06:47.494 --> 06:49.844
Oh, come on, honey.
I'm-I'm late for work.

06:49.887 --> 06:51.019
[entry bells chime]

06:51.062 --> 06:52.760
-E-Excuse me, lady.
-Yes?

06:52.803 --> 06:54.675
Look, I-I must get
those pants off you.

06:54.718 --> 06:57.678
No! I-I'm sorry. Uh, from you.
[chuckles]

06:57.721 --> 06:59.462
Oh, these tenna pants?

06:59.506 --> 07:01.421
Exactly. Yes.

07:01.464 --> 07:03.118
I'll give you more money
than you paid for them.

07:03.161 --> 07:04.728
No, I'm sorry.

07:04.772 --> 07:06.904
I feel I look my best
when I'm relaxed,

07:06.948 --> 07:08.602
and these will relax me.

07:08.645 --> 07:10.168
Wait, wait, wait.
I'll trade services for them.

07:10.212 --> 07:12.040
Uh, l-let me service you.

07:12.083 --> 07:13.911
I'll-I'll wash your dog
or your kids or your car

07:13.955 --> 07:17.349
or-or you. Wh-Whatever.
I just-I just need those pants.

07:17.393 --> 07:20.222
Dude, this is not tenna.

07:21.528 --> 07:24.444
Okay, nicely played,
sweatpants lady.

07:24.487 --> 07:26.576
Seems like I may need
to pay a little visit

07:26.620 --> 07:29.100
to the Bespectacled Dentist.

07:30.972 --> 07:33.496
I can't believe
we got to find mom a gift.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.846
We areher gift, right?

07:35.890 --> 07:37.195
Look at us.

07:37.239 --> 07:38.980
Besides, I'm not
seeing anything good

07:39.023 --> 07:40.808
in any of Aunt Maggie's
cursed stuff.

07:40.851 --> 07:43.506
This charming stuff
ain't cursed.

07:43.550 --> 07:47.292
"Cursed Dybbuk Box."

07:47.336 --> 07:48.990
Hmm. See?

07:49.033 --> 07:50.426
Cute box.

07:50.470 --> 07:52.036
Look, a string of baby teeth.

07:52.080 --> 07:54.212
But she didn't have any kids.

07:54.256 --> 07:56.258
That's sexist of you, Todd.

07:56.301 --> 07:58.869
A woman doesn't
need to have the babies

07:58.913 --> 08:01.176
to wear baby teeth
around her neck.

08:01.219 --> 08:03.221
Man, I don't know what to do.

08:03.265 --> 08:04.614
What are you gonna get Mom?

08:04.658 --> 08:06.747
When I know, I'll know,
you know?

08:07.748 --> 08:10.751
I'm eating Mom's catfish.

08:13.623 --> 08:15.103
Tonya!

08:15.146 --> 08:17.714
We can make so much money
off this thing.

08:17.758 --> 08:19.542
We will get moderately rich.

08:19.586 --> 08:21.196
And it was a steal.

08:21.239 --> 08:24.808
Well, I dated the previous
owner, the ice cream man.

08:24.852 --> 08:26.244
He owed me.

08:26.288 --> 08:27.985
He told me he had a Popsicle,

08:28.029 --> 08:30.379
but it was more
like a Dippin' Dot.

08:33.208 --> 08:35.210
Mmm! [slurping]
Mmm!

08:35.253 --> 08:37.342
[humming a tune]

08:38.343 --> 08:41.390
Oh, oh, oh, oh.
Mmm! Mmm, mmm, mmm.

08:41.433 --> 08:43.261
[grunting]

08:49.659 --> 08:51.008
Whew!

08:55.622 --> 08:57.319
Ah. Oh!

08:57.362 --> 08:59.364
[grunts]
Brain freeze!

08:59.408 --> 09:02.106
Oh, I drank it all so fast,

09:02.150 --> 09:03.891
like Sonic the Huge Hog.

09:03.934 --> 09:06.197
I could drink a gallon of that.

09:06.241 --> 09:08.591
Oh, yeah? Prove it.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.375
FREDDIE:
No, no, no, no, look,

09:10.419 --> 09:11.768
I've checked eBay.

09:11.812 --> 09:13.422
You guys are the manufacturer
of the sweatpants,

09:13.465 --> 09:15.772
so just tell me
what to do next, please.

09:15.816 --> 09:17.208
Look, man.

09:17.252 --> 09:19.167
We had to discontinue
our entire line of clothing

09:19.210 --> 09:20.821
due to a huge fire
at our garment factory

09:20.864 --> 09:22.126
in Bangladesh.

09:22.170 --> 09:23.519
Lots of people died.

09:23.563 --> 09:26.043
Oh, this is a terrible tragedy.

09:26.087 --> 09:28.916
A-And, you know, I'm sorry
to hear about whatever it was

09:28.959 --> 09:30.352
that happened to you guys, too.

09:31.309 --> 09:34.704
Oof! Oh, where's
this perfect gift, my man?

09:34.748 --> 09:36.880
Oh, it's coming, buddy.
Uh, yeah.

09:36.924 --> 09:38.186
They've just become, you know,

09:38.229 --> 09:40.405
like, an even cooler
challenge for me, so...

09:40.449 --> 09:41.798
Let's make this interesting.

09:41.842 --> 09:43.495
If you don't get
those sweatpants

09:43.539 --> 09:46.107
then we don't have to come up
with a gift idea for Mom

09:46.150 --> 09:49.023
and we all get her gift cards
to Sonic with your cash.

09:49.066 --> 09:50.851
Oh, I'll take that deal.

09:50.894 --> 09:54.419
Now, which outfit says
"dental patient"?

10:03.864 --> 10:05.430
Okay, Mister...

10:05.474 --> 10:06.997
Jeremy Spoken.

10:07.041 --> 10:09.434
Uh, let's see,
wh-what's your problem?

10:09.478 --> 10:10.914
Eh, just a cleaning
and checkup.

10:10.958 --> 10:14.657
Hey, look, we both like wacky,
colorful frames.

10:14.701 --> 10:16.006
-[chuckles]
-Yes, yes. Yes.

10:16.050 --> 10:17.573
O-O-Open wide, please.

10:17.617 --> 10:20.489
But you're very
professional-looking, otherwise.

10:20.532 --> 10:21.882
[slurps saliva]

10:21.925 --> 10:22.665
Not like you're wearing
sweatpants or anything.

10:23.710 --> 10:26.277
Do you like sweatpants
on people?

10:26.321 --> 10:28.279
Oh, I-I don't know.

10:28.323 --> 10:29.672
Spit, please.

10:29.716 --> 10:31.718
Yeah, tell me about it.

10:31.761 --> 10:33.850
Women look like dog shit
in sweatpants.

10:33.894 --> 10:35.939
Don't you think sweatpants
are an undesirable thing

10:35.983 --> 10:37.767
for women to wear?
I mean... [chuckles]

10:37.811 --> 10:40.988
It does kind of rub me the wrong
way, now that you mention it.

10:41.031 --> 10:42.598
Right!

10:42.642 --> 10:44.818
Yeah, guys like us
in cool glasses like ours--

10:44.861 --> 10:48.082
we'd never want to have sex
with a sweatpants lady.

10:48.125 --> 10:50.084
I'd be in flaccid city,
wouldn't you?

10:50.127 --> 10:52.782
Flaccid city.
Oh, yes.

10:52.826 --> 10:56.394
I have spent some nights there,
let me tell you.

10:56.438 --> 10:58.919
Sadly, I have.

10:58.962 --> 11:01.661
Man, if my wife
got sweatpants...

11:01.704 --> 11:04.751
[scoffs] I'd throw them
in the trash. Like, tonight.

11:04.794 --> 11:08.189
Which is your
trash night, y-yeah?

11:11.975 --> 11:13.934
♪

11:15.979 --> 11:19.113
DEBBIE:
Come get your day-drunk on!

11:19.156 --> 11:22.638
Margaritas, piña coladas,
frozens and straights.

11:22.682 --> 11:23.987
Let's go!

11:24.031 --> 11:26.294
Hey, that truck
ain't street legal.

11:26.337 --> 11:28.905
You need a license
to sell food or drink,

11:28.949 --> 11:30.733
and you can't sell alcohol.

11:30.777 --> 11:31.821
So, what-- you don't want one?

11:31.865 --> 11:33.736
No, no, I...

11:33.780 --> 11:36.043
-I want one.
-And give me a double.

11:37.827 --> 11:39.263
Here you go. Yep.

11:39.307 --> 11:41.831
Yep. Mm-hmm.
Good. Yes.

11:41.875 --> 11:43.746
Yes, yes.
Next. Next.

11:43.790 --> 11:45.313
Next.

11:45.356 --> 11:47.097
[horse whinnies]

11:48.838 --> 11:51.188
Ooh-ooh, uh-oh, time-out.
[chuckles]

11:51.232 --> 11:53.234
Y'all got a license
to sling drink?

11:53.277 --> 11:55.279
Oh, shit.
The fuzz!

11:55.323 --> 11:57.064
Whoa!

11:57.107 --> 12:00.067
ooh, hot damn, horsey.

12:00.110 --> 12:02.591
We got ourselves
a challenge in town.

12:02.634 --> 12:03.940
Giddyup.

12:06.638 --> 12:08.640
[grunting]

12:08.684 --> 12:10.381
Hyah!

12:10.425 --> 12:11.382
[exhales]

12:11.426 --> 12:14.168
Look at all this cash!

12:14.211 --> 12:17.084
Here's how you back
onto the south side.

12:17.127 --> 12:21.305
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,
but we just outran the cops.

12:21.349 --> 12:23.220
Maybe I went too far
with this one.

12:23.264 --> 12:24.787
Oh, bullshit.

12:24.831 --> 12:27.094
That was exactly
what I Wanted to happen.

12:27.137 --> 12:28.704
It was fun.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.532
Remember having fun?

12:30.575 --> 12:32.273
Since you moved out here
to the north side,

12:32.316 --> 12:33.709
you're so serious.

12:33.753 --> 12:36.756
You're all like,
"I lost my great job.

12:36.799 --> 12:39.410
"My great house.
My family is sad.

12:39.454 --> 12:41.804
Boo-hoo!" Fuck that.

12:41.848 --> 12:45.286
You are only once.

12:45.329 --> 12:47.854
Only once what?

12:47.897 --> 12:49.725
You.

12:53.468 --> 12:54.904
[trash rattling]

12:54.948 --> 12:57.385
Where are those
sweatpants, damn it?

12:57.428 --> 12:59.561
Did he not follow
my subtle manipulations?

12:59.604 --> 13:01.606
-What happened?
-[crying]

13:01.650 --> 13:03.391
No, you listen to me!

13:03.434 --> 13:04.871
I want a divorce!

13:04.914 --> 13:07.438
Well, if that's
how you feel about it...

13:11.878 --> 13:14.402
Oh, you better not get
nacho cheese on those pants

13:14.445 --> 13:16.012
before Debbie has the chance to.

13:16.056 --> 13:17.144
Shit!

13:19.668 --> 13:21.104
Hey.

13:21.148 --> 13:22.671
Oh, ho, ho.

13:22.714 --> 13:25.456
Hey, let's go to "lunch"
again, huh?

13:25.500 --> 13:27.110
I don't know, man.

13:27.154 --> 13:29.939
I mean, we drew some serious
heat on that last run.

13:29.983 --> 13:33.508
Yes, but this time
they won't be chasing us.

13:33.551 --> 13:35.989
[chuckles]

13:36.032 --> 13:37.120
[whistles]

13:37.164 --> 13:38.426
Nice.

13:38.469 --> 13:40.689
But I can't be Zorro.
I'm white.

13:40.732 --> 13:42.604
Bitch, this one's mine.

13:42.647 --> 13:45.302
I got one for you, too,
